  "prompt": "What is the temperature on the planet Mercury at the demarcation point between light and dark?",
  "response": "The temperature on Mercury at the demarcation line between light and dark, also known as the terminator, can vary significantly. Because Mercury has a very thin atmosphere, it cannot retain heat, and temperatures can fluctuate dramatically.\n\nDuring the day, temperatures on the side of Mercury that is facing the Sun can reach up to about 430 degrees Celsius (800 degrees Fahrenheit). Conversely, at night, temperatures on the dark side can plummet to around -180 degrees Celsius (-290 degrees Fahrenheit).\n\nAt the terminator, where sunlight meets shadow, temperatures would fall between these extremes, typically ranging from around 0 degrees Celsius (32 degrees Fahrenheit) to about 100 degrees Celsius (212 degrees Fahrenheit), depending on the specific conditions and location at that point on the surface. However, precise temperatures can vary based on local topography and other factors.",
